shortDescription: We have an operative in place in a covert {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} research facility, and for the past year they've been gathering sensitive research data for us. They've notified us that they're ready for us to extract the data, and we need a deniable force to arrange that extraction. The research facility is not connected to any data networks, and all the secure laboratories are far enough underground that wireless data signals are blocked. To get the information out, we're going to need to position a satellite receiver directly above the site. Your task will be to place positioning beacons to allow the satellite to lock on to the research data signal and download it.
longDescription: This sounds like a messy scenario, Commander. That satellite is only going to be overhead for a short time, and this place is going to be very heavily guarded.

dialogueContent.words: Commander, I'll try to keep this brief, because there's a lot happening on this one.
You need to move into position in three marked locations, here...
Here...
And here. You'll have to station a unit in each location long enough to get the beacon deployed.
Expect significant {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} resistance. They'll try to force you out of the targeting regions.
We're on a very tight schedule, Commander -- the satellite will only be overhead for a short time, and if we don't have the beacons up in time, no data, and no payday.
After the data has been uploaded, you'll get confirmation and you can make for the evac point. Sumire will be on station to pull you out of there.
Watch yourself, Commander. I saw a hell of a lot of opposition on the way in.
Is everyone aboard? Let's get the hell out of here.
That's it, Commander. We have to scrub the mission. Unfortunate.
I'm getting a signal from the satellite, Commander. They've locked on to the beacons successfully.
BEGINNING DATA TRANSMISSION.
Okay, Farah, give me a heads-up when they're done, and I'll move in for the pickup.
Alpha beacon deployed, Commander. Good work.
Bravo beacon deployed, Commander.
Charlie beacon deployed.
Attention all {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} forces: we believe the hostiles are attempting to place targeting beacons. Intercept them immediately!
